{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Instancer-1.3/mops_cloner_03.svg", "type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "Instancer", "version": "1.3", "namespace": "MOPS"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Instancer"], "extent": [0, 19]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Copies objects to various patterns, or onto a curve or mesh."], "extent": [55, 123]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The MOPs Instancer generates MOPs packed primitives and distributes them in various ways. Each distribution type has its own set of parameters.\nAny number of objects can be input into the Instancer; the Index Attribute and Indexing Mode parameters determine which of the input objects is copied to each point.\nThe objects that are generated are standard Houdini Packed Primitives, with a few extra attributes added for use with the rest of the MOPs system. "], "extent": [123, 582]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [582, 594], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Instancing"], "extent": [594, 612], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Indexing Mode"], "extent": [612, 628], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which indexes are generated, to determine which input object is copied to each point. This creates the i@mops_index point attribute."], "extent": [648, 804]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "index_mode"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Index Random Seed"], "extent": [804, 823], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When using the Random indexing mode, the random seed used to determine i@mops_index."], "extent": [843, 937]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "index_seed"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Index Attribute"], "extent": [937, 954], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When using the Input Mesh distribution method, you can provide an integer point attribute from the Input Mesh that will be used to create i@mops_index. Hint: You can use a MOPs Index From Attribute SOP to create this attribute on your Input Mesh."], "extent": [974, 1226]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "index_attr"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Quick Add Objects"], "extent": [1226, 1245], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["You can quickly add objects to the Instancer by picking them using the list button, or by simply dragging them into the parameter box."], "extent": [1264, 1408]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "quick_add"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Global Options"], "extent": [1408, 1431], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Points Only (No Instances)"], "extent": [1431, 1460], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Only arrange points with the appropriate attributes; don\u2019t actually generate any packed primitives. You can use this if you intend to copy objects to the points later using Copy to Points."], "extent": [1481, 1679]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "points_only"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Display As"], "extent": [1679, 1691], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The display method to use when showing the instanced primitives in the viewport."], "extent": [1712, 1802]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "viewportlod"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Transform Type"], "extent": [1802, 1818], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When loading SOPs into the Instancer, the method by which the objects are merged into the current Object network. See the Object Merge SOP for details."], "extent": [1837, 1998]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "xformtype"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Pack From Default"], "extent": [1998, 2017], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When connecting new inputs, the default packed pivot to use for the input. See ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Pack From"]}, " in the Instance Objects Block."], "extent": [2042, 2173]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "packfromdefault"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Material Overrides"], "extent": [2173, 2200], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable the Material Override parameters for the Instance Objects."], "extent": [2231, 2306]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_material_overrides"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Transfer Attributes"], "extent": [2306, 2327], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A list of attributes to transfer from the source geometry to the newly-generated packed primitives."], "extent": [2356, 2463]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "transfer_attributes"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Global Transform"], "extent": [2463, 2488], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The transforms defined here will apply to all instanced objects individually."], "extent": [2488, 2568]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Instance Objects Block"], "extent": [2568, 2603], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Instance Objects"], "extent": [2603, 2622], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A multiparm list of objects to generate with the Instancer."], "extent": [2647, 2716]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Instance Objects"], "extent": [2716, 2745], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Instance Type"], "extent": [2745, 2769], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The type of object to instance; either a SOP or Object, or a File (.bgeo or .abc)."], "extent": [2796, 2892]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instancetype#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Path"], "extent": [2892, 2902], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The path to the SOP or object to instance."], "extent": [2929, 2989]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instancepath#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["File Path"], "extent": [2989, 3004], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The path to the .bgeo or .abc file to instance. Bgeo files will be loaded as a Packed Disk Sequence."], "extent": [3035, 3153]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instancefilepath#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Cycle Method"], "extent": [3153, 3171], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The method used to cycle file sequences or Alembics."], "extent": [3195, 3265]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "cycletype#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Frame Range"], "extent": [3265, 3282], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The starting and ending frame of the sequence."], "extent": [3303, 3367]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "frange#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Frame Select"], "extent": [3367, 3385], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The method by which to choose the frame to load for each instance. There are two modes available:"], "extent": [3411, 3526]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Frame Number: You can directly set a frame number (such as @Frame) via the Frame Number attribute."], "extent": [3526, 3635]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Attribute: You can use a point attribute from the Template Object (if you are using Mesh or Curve instancing modes), specified via the Frame Attribute."], "extent": [3635, 3802]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "frameselect#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Probability"], "extent": [3802, 3819], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The weighted probability of each instance type. Lower numbers are less likely to appear in the Random Indexing mode."], "extent": [3854, 3984]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instance_probability#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Pack From"], "extent": [3984, 3999], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Where the default pivot for the packed primitive should be placed: at the centroid of the instance geometry, or at the world origin.        "], "extent": [4023, 4181]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "pack_from#"}}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Material Override"], "extent": [4181, 4204], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The material to apply to the instances under this path. Only active if ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Enable Material Overrides"]}, " is enabled; otherwise the material already applied to the SOP or object is used."], "extent": [4236, 4433]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instance_material#"}}], "container": true}]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "instanceobjects"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distribution"], "extent": [4433, 4452], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distribution Type"], "extent": [4452, 4472], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The distribution method to use for positioning and orienting objects. There are several modes available:"], "extent": [4498, 4612]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Linear: Arrange the instances in a straight line."], "extent": [4612, 4668]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Radial: Arrange the instances in a circle or spiral pattern."], "extent": [4668, 4735]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Spherical: Arrange the instances in a spherical pattern."], "extent": [4735, 4798]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Grid: Arrange the instances in a 2D grid or 3D matrix pattern."], "extent": [4798, 4867]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Mesh: Arrange the instances using a mesh."], "extent": [4867, 4915]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Curve: Arrange the instances along a NURBS or polyline curve."], "extent": [4915, 4983]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Honeycomb: Arrange the instances in a hexagonal pattern."], "extent": [4983, 5047]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "distro_type"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Template Object"], "extent": [5047, 5064], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The object to distribute Instances on."], "extent": [5083, 5131]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "inputMesh"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Template Group"], "extent": [5131, 5147], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Distribute Instances only on this group of the Template Object."], "extent": [5171, 5244]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "inputMeshGroup"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Template Rest Frame"], "extent": [5244, 5265], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When instancing onto an animated mesh, the frame to use as the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["rest"]}, " (default) frame. Instances will automatically interpolate their positions and orientations on an animated mesh, based on this default state. \n    If your template mesh has a changing point count, you will probably want to set this to @Frame in order to update the topology from the source."], "extent": [5294, 5668]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "template_rest_frame"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distribution Types"], "extent": [5668, 5693], "body": [{"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Linear"], "extent": [5693, 5719], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Points"], "extent": [5719, 5738], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points dividing the line segment."], "extent": [5762, 5819]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "linear_npoints"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Linear Mode"], "extent": [5819, 5832], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which to define the line. There are two options"], "extent": [5853, 5920], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Distance / Direction: Draw a line from an origin point towards a given direction vector, scaled by the Length parameter."], "extent": [5920, 6051]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Start / End: Draw a line between the two given points in space."], "extent": [6051, 6134]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "linear_mode"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Center at Origin"], "extent": [6134, 6152], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If enabled, always place the center of the line segment at the world origin."], "extent": [6182, 6268]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "linear_center_origin"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Orient"], "extent": [6268, 6285], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If Align is enabled, orient instances to the generated line. See ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Orient_Curve-1.0", "type": "link", "text": ["MOPs Orient Curve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Orient_Curve-1.0.html"}, " for details."], "extent": [6285, 6417]}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Radial"], "extent": [6417, 6432], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Points"], "extent": [6432, 6451], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points defining the circle."], "extent": [6475, 6522]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_npoints"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Options"], "extent": [6522, 6540], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Orientation"], "extent": [6540, 6558], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The orientation of the circle to clone on."], "extent": [6581, 6633]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_orient"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Arc Angles"], "extent": [6633, 6645], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The starting and ending angles of an open arc."], "extent": [6689, 6745]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "beginradial_rangle endradial_angle"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius"], "extent": [6745, 6753], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The u and v radius of the circle or ellipse."], "extent": [6792, 6846]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_radiusx radial_radiusy"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Uniform Scale"], "extent": [6846, 6861], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A scalar on the radius of the circle."], "extent": [6883, 6933]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_scale"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Divisions"], "extent": [6933, 6944], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points along the arc (not to be confused with the number of instance points). Higher numbers make smoother arcs."], "extent": [6970, 7102]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_divisions"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Center"], "extent": [7102, 7111], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The center of the generated circle."], "extent": [7129, 7174]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "tx ty tz"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotate"], "extent": [7174, 7182], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The Euler angles to apply to the circle\u2019s rotation."], "extent": [7200, 7261]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "rx ry rz"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Orient"], "extent": [7261, 7278], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align"], "extent": [7278, 7290], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Align copies to the arc."], "extent": [7312, 7346]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_align"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align Type"], "extent": [7346, 7358], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which to align instances"], "extent": [7385, 7429], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["To Center: Instances face inwards (or outwards, depending on the Invert Normal parameter) to the center."], "extent": [7429, 7544]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Along Perimeter: Instances face along the running edge of the circle."], "extent": [7544, 7633]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Orient_Curve-1.0", "type": "link", "text": ["MOPs Orient Curve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Orient_Curve-1.0.html"}, " for details on the other parameters."], "extent": [7633, 7735]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "radial_align_type"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Spherical"], "extent": [7735, 7753], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Points"], "extent": [7753, 7772], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points to generate on the sphere."], "extent": [7796, 7853]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_npoints"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sphere Options"], "extent": [7853, 7878], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius"], "extent": [7878, 7891], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The radius of the sphere."], "extent": [7914, 7949]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_radius"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cone Angle"], "extent": [7949, 7961], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The angle over which to distribute instances, relative to the Cone Direction vector. A value of 90 degrees would distribute instances in a hemisphere around the Cone Direction. The default value of 180 distributes around a complete sphere."], "extent": [7982, 8231]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_cone"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Cone Direction"], "extent": [8231, 8247], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The axis around which the instances are distributed, depending on the Cone Angle."], "extent": [8279, 8370]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_cone_direction "}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align"], "extent": [8370, 8377], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Align clones to the surface of the sphere."], "extent": [8399, 8451]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_align"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Align to Equator"], "extent": [8451, 8469], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "Align clones so that they circle the equator of the sphere rather than facing the center."}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill Sphere"], "extent": [8573, 8586], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If enabled, instances are generated within the volume of the sphere as well as on the surface."], "extent": [8610, 8714]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_sphere_fill"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 4, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scatter Options"], "extent": [8714, 8740], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scatter Seed"], "extent": [8740, 8755], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The random seed used for distributing spherical instances."], "extent": [8776, 8844]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "sphere_seed"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Relax Iterations"], "extent": [8844, 8862], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["See the Scatter SOP for more information."], "extent": [8888, 8939]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "relaxiterations3"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale Radii By"], "extent": [8939, 8955], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["See the Scatter SOP for more information."], "extent": [8978, 9029]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "scaleradiiby3"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Max Relax Radius"], "extent": [9029, 9047], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["See the Scatter SOP for more information."], "extent": [9066, 9122]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "maxradius"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Grid"], "extent": [9122, 9135], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Distribution Type"], "extent": [9135, 9155], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which to generate instances on the grid:"], "extent": [9182, 9241]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Fixed Size: determine a total size for the grid, and use the Step parameter to control the distance between instances. "], "extent": [9241, 9367]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Fixed Number: determine a specific number of instances along each axis, and use the Distance parameter to adjust the distance between them."], "extent": [9367, 9514]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "grid_distrib_type"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Size"], "extent": [9514, 9520], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["(Fixed Size) The total size of the grid."], "ex